title: Add Z.ai MCP websearch and webfetch tools with config integration
---
## Summary
Add native support for Z.ai's MCP-powered websearch and webfetch tools. These should be exposed as first-class tools in clawq, configured via a dedicated config section, and automatically reuse existing `zai` or `zai_coding` API keys.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Config schema has new `zai_mcp` object with fields for enabling/configuring websearch and webfetch
- If `zai_mcp` is enabled but no explicit API key is set, auto-detect and reuse `providers.zai.api_key` or `providers.zai_coding.api_key`
- Two new tools: `zai_websearch` and `zai_webfetch` (or similar naming)
- Tools call Z.ai's MCP endpoints for websearch/webfetch functionality
- Documentation updated in llms-full.txt and relevant docs

## Research Needed
- Find Z.ai MCP websearch/webfetch API docs (URLs, request/response formats)
- Determine authentication method (API key in header vs other)
- Check rate limits and pricing if applicable

## Files to Modify
- src/runtime_config.ml (add zai_mcp config type)
- src/config_loader.ml (parse zai_mcp config)
- src/tools_builtin.ml (add websearch/webfetch tool implementations)
- src/provider.ml or src/http_client.ml (API calls if needed)
- docs/public/llms-full.txt

## Delegation
Use opencode glm-5 to research Z.ai MCP docs and implement.
